<div type="definition">
<p>ROOM or BUILDING USED FOR DEFECATION.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for a toilet is cè 廁.</p>
<p>2. Bìng 庰 refers to the toilet as being blocked off.</p>
<p>3. Yǎn 偃 refers to the toilet as hiding what is going on inside.</p>
<p>4. Hùn 溷／圂 refers to the toilet as a dirty place.</p>
<p>5. Xuān 軒 refers to the toilet as being comparable in shape to a xuān 軒 carriage which hides those who ride on it.</p>
        </div>
